---
export const prerender = true

import PageIntro from '@/components/PageIntro.astro'
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { CACHE_CONTROL } from '@/utils/cache-control'
import { SITE_DOMAIN } from '@/utils/meta'

Astro.response.headers.set('Cache-Control', CACHE_CONTROL.staticPage)
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="How loke.dev and related sites handle infrastructure logs, aggregate analytics events, contact messages, and affiliate click measurement."
  url={`${SITE_DOMAIN}/privacy`}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 md:py-20">
    <PageIntro
      eyebrow="Privacy"
      title="Measure useful actions, not personal browsing profiles."
      description="This notice covers loke.dev and related projects that send aggregate events to loke.dev, including Shuffleworks and FlareCheck."
    />

    <div class="prose prose-invert mt-12 max-w-none">
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 24 July 2026.</p>

      <h2>Who operates these sites</h2>
      <p>
        Loke operates these personal projects from Sweden. Questions, objections, and
        privacy requests can be sent through the <a href="/contact">contact page</a> or to
        <a href="mailto:hi@loke.dev">hi@loke.dev</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Infrastructure and security logs</h2>
      <p>
        The sites use Cloudflare for hosting, delivery, security, and Worker execution.
        Like other web infrastructure, Cloudflare receives network information needed to
        deliver a request, such as an IP address, user agent, requested URL, and security
        metadata. Some of that information may appear temporarily in infrastructure logs
        according to the Cloudflare account settings and retention terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Aggregate site and event analytics</h2>
      <p>
        The sites may use Cloudflare Web Analytics for aggregate traffic and performance
        reporting. The custom event collector records only an approved event name, site,
        page path, placement, target, campaign label, and count. Examples include a
        successful command copy, a tool action, a completed shuffle, or an outbound
        partner click.
      </p>
      <p>
        The application event payload does not include an email address, account ID, raw
        IP address, raw user agent, advertising identifier, or browser fingerprint. The
        collector does not set a cookie or use local storage. Infrastructure providers
        still process the network request as described above.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate and outbound links</h2>
      <p>
        Some product links pass through a short loke.dev redirect. The redirect records
        the product and link placement before sending the browser to the provider. A
        commission-capable link is disclosed separately under the
        <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">affiliate and editorial policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact messages and error reports</h2>
      <p>
        A contact message contains the name, email address, and message supplied by the
        sender. Resend processes the email delivery so the message can be answered. When
        error monitoring is configured, Sentry may process technical diagnostics needed
        to investigate failures. Do not put secrets or sensitive personal information in
        a contact message.
      </p>

      <h2>Service providers and external sites</h2>
      <p>
        Current infrastructure and operational providers may include Cloudflare for
        delivery and analytics, Sanity for published content, Resend for contact email,
        and Sentry for error diagnostics. Following an external or affiliate link makes
        the destination provider responsible for its own processing under its privacy
        notice.
      </p>

      <h2>Retention and choices</h2>
      <p>
        Aggregate application events are kept only as long as they are useful for product
        and affiliate measurement. Analytics Engine currently has a three-month data
        window when enabled. Infrastructure logs follow provider and account retention
        settings. Contact messages are retained only as needed to respond, maintain
        reasonable records, or meet a legal obligation.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can block browser analytics requests using browser privacy controls. You may
        also ask about access, correction, deletion, restriction, or objection through
        the contact details above. A request may require enough information to locate the
        relevant record; anonymous aggregate events cannot normally be connected back to
        a particular visitor.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
